                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate Inner Sight</strong> &mdash; Attack marked enemies with Twisting Blades to fill the Inner Sight meter. Once full, you gain unlimited Energy for a duration.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Cast Rain of Arrows during Inner Sight</strong> &mdash; With unlimited Energy, spam Rain of Arrows continuously to blanket the screen in projectiles. This is your primary damage window.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Maintain Dark Shroud</strong> &mdash; Keep Dark Shroud active at all times for stacking damage reduction. Recast whenever shadow charges are consumed.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Use Dash for positioning</strong> &mdash; Dash into packs to maximize Rain of Arrows projectile hits. Beastfall Boots grant movement speed boost after each Dash.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Twisting Blades filler</strong> &mdash; Between Rain of Arrows cooldowns, use Twisting Blades to deal damage, build Inner Sight, and apply Vulnerable via Artful Initiative.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Shadow Step for emergencies</strong> &mdash; Use Shadow Step to break crowd control or dodge one-shot mechanics. The Unstoppable window can save your life.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Concealment for resets</strong> &mdash; When overwhelmed or waiting for Ultimate cooldown, pop Concealment for invisibility and safety. Use the downtime to rebuild resources.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Gameplay Tips</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Scoundrel's Leathers is mandatory.</strong>
                    <p>Without Scoundrel's Leathers, Rain of Arrows has too much downtime. The chest piece's CDR synergy with Inner Sight is the only way to maintain consistent Ultimate uptime. Do not attempt this build without it.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Inner Sight is your damage window.</strong>
                    <p>The unlimited Energy from Inner Sight allows you to spam Rain of Arrows without resource concerns. Plan your positioning and cooldowns around Inner Sight phases for maximum efficiency.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Stack CDR aggressively.</strong>
                    <p>Every point of CDR translates directly to more Rain of Arrows uptime. Prioritize CDR on gear, tempering, and Paragon. More uptime means exponentially more damage.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Position in the middle of packs.</strong>
                    <p>Rain of Arrows has a fixed radius. Standing in the center of enemy groups ensures every projectile finds a target. Use Dash to dive in, then rain death from the center.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Branching Volleys is non-negotiable.</strong>
                    <p>Aspect of Branching Volleys is what transforms Rain of Arrows into a screen-wide delete button. Without it, the coverage is mediocre. This aspect is mandatory for the build to function.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
